<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-365] qos_threshold_rr is misspelled twice</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-365</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The term qos_threshold_rr is misspelled in both these lines in section 18.5.2 of the current Lustre 2.x manual at &lt;a href=&quot;https://wiki.hpdd.intel.com/display/PUB/Documentation&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://wiki.hpdd.intel.com/display/PUB/Documentation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  To set the qos_threshold_r to 25, enter this command on the MGS:&lt;br/&gt;
  lctl set_param lov.fsname-mdtlov.quos_threshold_rr=25&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Documentation</environment>
